 and christian charity and if they wanted to run it that way, i didn&amp;#39;t want any part of it.</content><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/8752543/109915381192378495/comments/default/6602018339798363893'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/8752543/109915381192378495/comments/default/6602018339798363893'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='http://guide2homelessness.blogspot.com/2004/10/shelters-are-for-someone-else-part-2.html?showComment=1320037821011#c6602018339798363893' title=''/><author><name>Anonymous</name><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='http://img1.blogblog.com/img/blank.gif'/></author><thr:in-reply-to xmlns:thr='http://purl.org/syndication/thread/1.0' href='http://guide2homelessness.blogspot.com/2004/10/shelters-are-for-someone-else-part-2.html' ref='tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-8752543.post-109915381192378495' source='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/8752543/posts/default/109915381192378495' type='text/html'/><gd:extendedProperty name="blogger.itemClass" value="pid-1699260275"/><gd:extendedProperty name="blogger.displayTime" value="10:10 PM"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-8752543.post-5236118173043435774</id><published>2011-06-05T17:20:30.037-07:00</published><updated>2011-06-05T17:20:30.037-07:00</updated><title type='text'>About an hour ago someone left a comment telling m...</title><content type='html'>About an hour ago someone left a comment telling me about all the things he believed homeless people are. I haven&amp;#39;t published it because freedom of speech doesn&amp;#39;t extend into my blog space, and I am not going to have my readers who are homeless subjected to hateful statements. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Don&amp;#39;t think of this blog as a public square. Think of it as my home. You wouldn&amp;#39;t want me to come into your home and trash the place. (Trust me, you wouldn&amp;#39;t. I can knock a house down to the foundations.) Don&amp;#39;t come into my home with hate.</content><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/8752543/109915381192378495/comments/default/5236118173043435774'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/8752543/109915381192378495/comments/default/5236118173043435774'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='http://guide2homelessness.blogspot.com/2004/10/shelters-are-for-someone-else-part-2.html?showComment=1307319630037#c5236118173043435774' title=''/><author><name>Mobile Homemaker</name><uri>http://www.blogger.com/profile/01514644458931963694</uri><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='http://img1.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif'/></author><thr:in-reply-to xmlns:thr='http://purl.org/syndication/thread/1.0' href='http://guide2homelessness.blogspot.com/2004/10/shelters-are-for-someone-else-part-2.html' ref='tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-8752543.post-109915381192378495' source='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/8752543/posts/default/109915381192378495' type='text/html'/><gd:extendedProperty name="blogger.itemClass" value="pid-536784198"/><gd:extendedProperty name="blogger.displayTime" value="5:20 PM"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-8752543.post-4831358810815066592</id><published>2011-05-30T21:54:05.372-07:00</published><updated>2011-05-30T21:54:05.372-07:00</updated><title type='text'>David, first I want to thank you for supporting my...</title><content type='html'>David, first I want to thank you for supporting my suspicions that all shelters, without exception, are like this one or worse. I wonder, why do you stay in them? Why do you couch surf? Can&amp;#39;t you get a cheap car and do it my way? Even if you have a suspended or revoked license, that only means you can&amp;#39;t drive the car. You could pay someone a couple of bucks to help you move it around. Isn&amp;#39;t there a better way than subjecting yourself to this horror?</content><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/8752543/109915381192378495/comments/default/4831358810815066592'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/8752543/109915381192378495/comments/default/4831358810815066592'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='http://guide2homelessness.blogspot.com/2004/10/shelters-are-for-someone-else-part-2.html?showComment=1306817645372#c4831358810815066592' title=''/><author><name>Mobile Homemaker</name><uri>http://www.blogger.com/profile/01514644458931963694</uri><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='http://img1.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif'/></author><thr:in-reply-to xmlns:thr='http://purl.org/syndication/thread/1.0' href='http://guide2homelessness.blogspot.com/2004/10/shelters-are-for-someone-else-part-2.html' ref='tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-8752543.post-109915381192378495' source='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/8752543/posts/default/109915381192378495' type='text/html'/><gd:extendedProperty name="blogger.itemClass" value="pid-536784198"/><gd:extendedProperty name="blogger.displayTime" value="9:54 PM"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-8752543.post-6737528334130782695</id><published>2011-05-30T21:10:25.082-07:00</published><updated>2011-05-30T21:10:25.082-07:00</updated><title type='text'>I&amp;#39;ve spent quite a bit of time in shelters. Be...</title><content type='html'>I&amp;#39;ve spent quite a bit of time in shelters. Between a pretty ugly criminal record and anxiety and depression issues, housing is hard for me to come by. What you describe here is the best of shelters. Even when you pay $5 a night, its just like this. The free shelters are worse. As you say, the people working and running the shelters have the best of intentions, but the result is what it is. Something to note: most of the first line shelter workers are homeless folks that have entered whatever &amp;#39;program&amp;#39; the shelter offers. I remember at the $5 shelter, a man named Dave who loved to threaten barring, even though he entered the shelter a couple days after me. But he entered the program, so he gained that power.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Shelters are horrific, degrading, paternalistic kindness at its finest. &amp;#39;m couch-surfing now, but if I hadn&amp;#39;t burnt the bridge at the $5 shelter by speaking my mind, I&amp;#39;d go back, cuz couch-surfing sucks, too. The whole situation is hideous.</content><link rel='edit' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/8752543/109915381192378495/comments/default/6737528334130782695'/><link rel='self' type='application/atom+xml' href='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/8752543/109915381192378495/comments/default/6737528334130782695'/><link rel='alternate' type='text/html' href='http://guide2homelessness.blogspot.com/2004/10/shelters-are-for-someone-else-part-2.html?showComment=1306815025082#c6737528334130782695' title=''/><author><name>David</name><uri>http://www.blogger.com/profile/15204191945608018879</uri><email>noreply@blogger.com</email><gd:image rel='http://schemas.google.com/g/2005#thumbnail' width='16' height='16' src='http://img1.blogblog.com/img/b16-rounded.gif'/></author><thr:in-reply-to xmlns:thr='http://purl.org/syndication/thread/1.0' href='http://guide2homelessness.blogspot.com/2004/10/shelters-are-for-someone-else-part-2.html' ref='tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-8752543.post-109915381192378495' source='http://www.blogger.com/feeds/8752543/posts/default/109915381192378495' type='text/html'/><gd:extendedProperty name="blogger.itemClass" value="pid-871059394"/><gd:extendedProperty name="blogger.displayTime" value="9:10 PM"/></entry><entry><id>tag:blogger.com,1999:blog-8752543.post-1908195658109574843</id><published>2010-11-18T17:40:13.105-08:0